MATCH_TOOL: Edit|Write
MATCH_PATTERN: apps/game-server/src/machines/__tests__/.+\.test\.ts$
ADVISORY: |
  Testing `dailySessionMachine` (L3) directly with `createActor()` will throw
  "Unable to send event to actor '#_parent'" the moment any action calls
  `sendParent(...)` — L3 has several (INTERNAL.READY, PUSH.PHASE, Events.Fact.RECORD).

  The canonical workaround is the parentWrapper pattern in
  `apps/game-server/src/machines/__tests__/l3-dm-invitations.test.ts:36-84`:

    const parentWrapper = setup({
      types: { context: {} as { l3Ref: any }, events: {} as any, input: {} as {...} },
      actors: { l3: dailySessionMachine },
    }).createMachine({
      id: 'test-parent',
      context: { l3Ref: null },
      initial: 'running',
      states: {
        running: {
          invoke: { id: 'l3-session', src: 'l3', input: ({ event }: any) => event.input || {} },
          on: { '*': {} },  // swallow facts/rejections the child emits upward
        },
        done: { type: 'final' },
      },
    } as any);

    function createL3Actor() {
      const parentActor = createActor(parentWrapper, { input: {...} });
      parentActor.start();
      return {
        send: (e) => parentActor.getSnapshot().children['l3-session']?.send(e),
        getL3Context: () => parentActor.getSnapshot().children['l3-session']?.getSnapshot().context,
      };
    }

  For pure context-shape tests (no sendParent triggered), `buildL3Context(input)` is
  exported from `l3-session.ts` and is simpler — see `l3-social-limits.test.ts`.

  Rule of thumb:
  - Testing initial context / selector over context → `buildL3Context` directly.
  - Testing event handling / guards / actions → parentWrapper + `createL3Actor` helper.
